Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.24,0:00:05.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Hello it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.24,0:00:05.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你好 我是斯科特-曼利
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.75,0:00:08.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Yesterday we took another step towards science fiction
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.75,0:00:08.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,昨天 我们又向科幻小说迈出了一步
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.32,0:00:14.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,when it was announced that the US Air Force Research Laboratory was going to start taking a serious look at
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.32,0:00:14.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当它宣布美国空军研究实验室将开始认真研究
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.87,0:00:22.25,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,suborbital transportation of materials cargo whatever around the world using rockets right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.87,0:00:22.25,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,使用火箭在世界范围内进行材料货物的亚轨道运输 对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.50,0:00:27.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I mean the official announcements talking about the this being a Vanguard program
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.50,0:00:27.03,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我的意思是 官方的公告说这是一个先锋计划
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.03,0:00:30.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,as part of their science and technology strategy for the next decade.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.03,0:00:30.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,作为他们未来十年的科学和技术战略的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.56,0:00:33.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And that Space Force would be the lead service for the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.56,0:00:33.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而太空部队将是该计划的主导部门
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.76,0:00:38.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And I'm not really sure what lead service means in this context
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.76,0:00:38.03,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我不太清楚在这种情况下主导服务意味着什么
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.03,0:00:43.25,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but I'm sure the concept of Space Force sending military assets around the world using rockets
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.03,0:00:43.25,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但我确信 太空部队使用火箭将军事资产送到世界各地的概念
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.25,0:00:45.38,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,sounds a lot like science fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.25,0:00:45.38,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,听起来很像科幻小说
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.98,0:00:49.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Well at least sending military hardware in that manner
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.98,0:00:49.03,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,嗯 至少以这种方式发送军事硬件
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.15,0:00:54.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,without intending them to well explode on arrival ICBMs, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.15,0:00:54.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而不打算让它们在抵达洲际弹道导弹上爆炸 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.64,0:01:00.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Sci-fI has things like Starship troopers dropping onto the battlefield and pods
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.64,0:01:00.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,科幻小说里有像星际飞船士兵投放到战场上的东西 还有吊舱
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.16,0:01:07.57,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and in the 1950s and 1960s the idea of deploying troops via rocket was actually investigated broadly
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.16,0:01:07.57,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在20世纪50年代和60年代 通过火箭部署部队的想法实际上得到了广泛研究
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.91,0:01:11.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it produced like this marvelous concept art showing something
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.91,0:01:11.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它产生了像这样奇妙的概念艺术 展示了一些东西
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.28,0:01:15.10,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,that would make Starship look pretty small in comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.28,0:01:15.10,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这将使 "星舰 "看起来相当小
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.68,0:01:18.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But in this case it's not about building anything new.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.68,0:01:18.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但在这种情况下 这并不是要建造什么新东西
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.88,0:01:23.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The official wording announcing the program specifically says
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.88,0:01:23.19,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,宣布该计划的官方措辞特别说到
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.20,0:01:27.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,that the Air Force Research Laboratory will lead a science and technology effort
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.20,0:01:27.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,空军研究实验室将领导一项科学和技术工作
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.68,0:01:31.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,to determine the viability and utility of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.68,0:01:31.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,以确定使用现有大型商业火箭的可行性和实用性
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.29,0:01:36.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,using existing large commercial rockets for the Department of Defense global logistics.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.29,0:01:36.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,使用现有的大型商业火箭用于国防部的全球物流
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.84,0:01:40.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So look this kind of restricts it to things that are already in existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.84,0:01:40.96,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以看起来这有点将它限制在已经存在的东西上
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.96,0:01:43.65,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's very likely just going to be a bunch of people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.96,0:01:43.65,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这很可能只是一群人
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.15,0:01:49.43,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,sitting in a room and doing math and running simulations playing Kerbal Space Program
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.15,0:01:49.43,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,坐在一个房间里 做数学题 运行模拟 玩Kerbal太空计划
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.43,0:01:52.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and writing a report based on what's commercially available.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.43,0:01:52.45,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并根据商业上可用的东西写一份报告
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.88,0:01:58.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And based on the current market the only thing that seriously fits the bill is SpaceX's Starship right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.88,0:01:58.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而根据目前的市场 唯一符合条件的是SpaceX的星际飞船
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.28,0:02:05.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I mean the concept art pretty much screams make it not quite look like SpaceX
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.28,0:02:05.45,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我的意思是 概念图几乎是在叫嚣着让它看起来不太像SpaceX
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.98,0:02:11.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and the truth is however the Starship is not really an ideal design for many technical reasons
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.98,0:02:11.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而事实是 由于许多技术原因 星际飞船并不是一个理想的设计
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.78,0:02:13.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but we'll get back to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.78,0:02:13.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但我们会回到这个问题上
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.40,0:02:18.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Right now the fastest way to move stuff around the world is probably aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.40,0:02:18.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 在世界范围内移动东西的最快方式可能是飞机
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.97,0:02:21.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Things like the C-130 Hercules, the C-5 Galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.97,0:02:21.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,像C-130大力士 C-5银河
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.92,0:02:23.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,These are subsonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.92,0:02:23.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这些都是亚音速的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.12,0:02:28.50,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,They will take a day to get around to the other side of the world with your precious cargo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.12,0:02:28.50,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它们需要一天的时间才能把你的珍贵货物运到世界的另一端
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.94,0:02:33.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But the US military already has bases all over the world
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.94,0:02:33.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但美国军方已经在世界各地拥有基地
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.66,0:02:37.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and so if you've got something that's needed to be transported over that distance
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.66,0:02:37.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 如果你有东西需要被运输到那么远的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.06,0:02:42.49,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it actually makes some sense to have caches of this stuff at bases around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.06,0:02:42.49,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,实际上 在世界各地的基地存放这些东西是有意义的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.14,0:02:45.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And the nice thing about air transport is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.14,0:02:45.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,空中运输的好处是
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.44,0:02:49.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it is actually possible to air drop some of these things into locations
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.44,0:02:49.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它实际上有可能将其中一些东西空投到需要的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.14,0:02:51.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,where it's needed and where the aircraft can't land.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.14,0:02:51.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在需要它的地方 而飞机不能降落
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.53,0:02:57.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So my question is is there a real need for suborbital transport
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.53,0:02:57.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以我的问题是 是否真的需要亚轨道运输？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.48,0:03:01.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which is again able to move stuff anywhere on the earth in under an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.48,0:03:01.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它又能在一小时内把东西送到地球上的任何地方
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.59,0:03:03.26,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And I'm very skeptical.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.59,0:03:03.26,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我非常怀疑
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.44,0:03:06.49,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I think the scenarios where it works are very narrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.44,0:03:06.49,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我认为它发挥作用的场景非常狭窄
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.72,0:03:09.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But the US Department of Defense has deep pockets
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.72,0:03:09.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但美国国防部有很深的口袋
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.04,0:03:14.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and might end up investing in something even if it never actually gets used.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.04,0:03:14.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并可能最终投资于一些东西 即使它实际上从未被使用
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.40,0:03:18.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Suborbital transportation makes the transport very fast
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.40,0:03:18.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,亚轨道运输使运输速度非常快
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.07,0:03:22.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but it still takes time to load and unload at each end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.07,0:03:22.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但它仍然需要时间在每一端进行装载和卸载
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.65,0:03:26.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And the loading time you also have to account for things like propellant loading time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.65,0:03:26.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且装载时间还必须考虑到推进剂装载时间等因素
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.39,0:03:29.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which is non-trivial for a 5000 ton rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.39,0:03:29.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,对于5000吨的火箭来说 这是非同小可的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.31,0:03:35.26,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You can't keep a cryogenically fueled Starship on the pad ready to go at a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.31,0:03:35.26,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你不可能把装有低温燃料的星际飞船放在平台上随时准备出发
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:39.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Notice it takes about 30 minutes to fuel up the Falcon 9
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:39.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,请注意 给猎鹰9号加燃料大约需要30分钟
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.11,0:03:42.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it will probably take longer to load up Starship with all its propellants.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.11,0:03:42.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并可能需要更长的时间来装载星际飞船的所有推进剂
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.77,0:03:45.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now it can be presumed that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.77,0:03:45.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在可以推测
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.37,0:03:51.38,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,the massive extra resources needed for suborbital delivery will make it much more expensive than aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.37,0:03:51.38,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,亚轨道运送所需的大量额外资源将使其比飞机昂贵得多
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.70,0:03:58.10,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Currently the Falcon 9 rideshare program costs of about 5000 dollars per kilogram.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.70,0:03:58.10,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,目前 "猎鹰9号 "共享项目的成本约为每公斤5000美元
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.56,0:04:02.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now the scale of something like Starship might reduce that to a fraction of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.56,0:04:02.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 像Starship这样的规模可能会将其减少到这个数字的一小部分
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.56,0:04:05.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Whatever you want to ship around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.56,0:04:05.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,无论你想在世界范围内运输什么
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.28,0:04:09.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it will have to justify this cost of getting there a day before other supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.28,0:04:09.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它将不得不证明比其他物资早一天到达那里的成本是合理的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.76,0:04:12.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And the good news of course on this is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.76,0:04:12.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当然 这方面的好消息是
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.24,0:04:17.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,that the US military has lots of stuff that costs more than five thousand dollars per kilogram.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.24,0:04:17.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,美国军方有很多东西 每公斤的成本超过5000美元
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.38,0:04:21.91,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So let's look at that glorious concept art again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.38,0:04:21.91,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 让我们再看看那幅光辉的概念图
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.91,0:04:26.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It shows trucks driving away from a rocket with red cross flags
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.91,0:04:26.00,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它显示了从火箭上开走的卡车 上面有红色的十字旗帜
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.02,0:04:29.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,suggesting that this monster rocket dropped into some disaster zone
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.02,0:04:29.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,暗示这个怪物火箭掉进了某个灾区
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.60,0:04:32.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,with materials to help the locals get back on their feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.60,0:04:32.40,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,带有帮助当地人重新站起来的材料
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.59,0:04:37.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And the US military is actually regularly involved in disaster relief operations
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.59,0:04:37.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而美国军队实际上经常参与救灾行动
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.34,0:04:41.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but if you're watching something like a hurricane or floods or bad weather
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.34,0:04:41.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但如果你看到的是像飓风、洪水或恶劣天气这样的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.04,0:04:47.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,then the odds are the planners already have enough of a head start to be preparing for the recovery
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.04,0:04:47.19,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么规划者已经有足够的先机为恢复做准备了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.38,0:04:51.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,by moving materials closer to the place they'll be needed as soon as landing as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.38,0:04:51.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,尽可能快地把物资运到需要的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.64,0:04:53.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Assuming that someone competent is in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.64,0:04:53.95,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,假设有能力的人在负责
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.32,0:04:58.63,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Earthquakes and tsunami on the other hand they don't have offer any warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.32,0:04:58.63,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,另一方面 地震和海啸是没有任何警告的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.63,0:05:00.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So sure there might be some advantage in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.63,0:05:00.81,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 可以肯定的是 在地震和海啸发生后的几个小时内 可能会有一些好处
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.82,0:05:05.91,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,getting relief to some people hours afterwards rather than days afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.82,0:05:05.91,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,让一些人在几小时后而不是几天后得到救济可能有一些好处
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.06,0:05:09.30,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But again this is very much a niche application.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.06,0:05:09.30,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但这又是一个非常小众的应用
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.23,0:05:13.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The image also shows a rocket landed vertically
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.23,0:05:13.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,该图片还显示了火箭垂直降落的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:16.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and this is what Starship intends to do
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:16.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而这正是Starship打算做的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.44,0:05:19.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but it's not really a great option for loading and unloading.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.44,0:05:19.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但对于装卸来说 这并不是一个真正的好选择
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.16,0:05:24.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Starship has to land vertically because the engines are in the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.16,0:05:24.00,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,星际飞船必须垂直着陆 因为引擎在底部
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.00,0:05:28.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it uses the same engines for boosting into orbit and for landing back from space
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.00,0:05:28.17,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且它使用相同的发动机来推动进入轨道和从太空降落回来
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.19,0:05:30.35,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because you're trying to optimize for the mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.19,0:05:30.35,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为你正试图对质量进行优化
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.89,0:05:33.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But let's be clear the wording surrounding the program
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.89,0:05:33.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但我们要清楚围绕该计划的措辞
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.08,0:05:38.49,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it does give them flexibility to consider other options from other contractors
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.08,0:05:38.49,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它确实给了他们灵活性来考虑来自其他承包商的其他方案
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:43.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,who might want to throw their hat in the ring if they smell some DoD contract money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:43.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,如果他们嗅到了国防部合同资金的味道 他们可能想把他们的帽子扔进戒指里
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.40,0:05:47.26,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,If you were wanting to build something more appropriate for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.40,0:05:47.26,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,如果你想建造一些更适合于
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.27,0:05:50.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,landing in an unprepared area and offloading cargo
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.27,0:05:50.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在没有准备好的地方降落并卸载货物
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.40,0:05:54.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I still don't think that parachutes are going to be a viable option simply
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.40,0:05:54.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我仍然不认为降落伞将是一个可行的选择 仅仅是
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.24,0:05:56.38,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because we're talking something very large.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.24,0:05:56.38,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为我们谈论的是非常大的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.87,0:06:01.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But redesigned rocket-based lander which puts the cargo closer to the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.87,0:06:01.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但重新设计的火箭着陆器 将货物放在离地面更近的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.59,0:06:07.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,would solve the massive problems of unloading cargo quickly from Starship after landing in the location
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.59,0:06:07.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,将会解决星际飞船着陆后迅速卸下货物的巨大问题
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.20,0:06:11.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which may not have any specialist cargo handling gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.20,0:06:11.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,可能没有任何专业的货物处理设备
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.17,0:06:17.73,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I mean on the other hand Starship might work well if you're delivering cargo between US bases
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.17,0:06:17.73,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我的意思是 另一方面 如果你在美国基地之间运送货物 星际飞船可能很好用
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.92,0:06:23.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but again if you're delivering it between bases you have to ask what kind of cargo is so valuable
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.92,0:06:23.03,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但是 如果你要在基地之间运送货物 你必须要问 什么样的货物是如此有价值的？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.18,0:06:27.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,that it isn't just cheaper to have extra copies on hand at bases around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.18,0:06:27.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,以至于在世界各地的基地都有额外的副本 这不是更便宜吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:32.91,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,One item actually which can't be easily copied is people
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:32.91,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,实际上 有一个项目是不容易复制的 那就是人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.36,0:06:37.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,if there's some situation that requires a specific person or specific group of people
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.36,0:06:37.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,如果有一些情况需要一个特定的人或特定的一群人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.65,0:06:41.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,to be on the ground in a specific place as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.65,0:06:41.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,尽快赶到一个特定的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.09,0:06:45.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Sure this is something that might actually work might offer an advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.09,0:06:45.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当然这是可能真正起作用的东西可能提供一个优势
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.91,0:06:51.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The 1960s concept are actually shows troops deploying via a giant inflatable slide
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.91,0:06:51.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,20世纪60年代的概念实际上显示了部队通过一个巨大的充气滑梯进行部署
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.72,0:06:53.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which seems sub-optimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.72,0:06:53.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这似乎是次优的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:57.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,After a rocket launch hot re-entry and fiery landing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:57.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在经历了火箭发射的高温再入和火热的着陆之后
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.36,0:07:01.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it would be unfortunate to injure yourself on a giant inflatable slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.36,0:07:01.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,如果在一个巨大的充气滑梯上受伤 那将是不幸的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.47,0:07:08.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The trajectory that a sub-orbital flight has to follow means that there's no flexibility on routes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.47,0:07:08.69,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,亚轨道飞行必须遵循的轨迹意味着在路线上没有灵活性
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.71,0:07:10.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You have to follow a great circle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.71,0:07:10.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你必须遵循一个大圆圈
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.16,0:07:15.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and that means the vehicle from certain destinations will override territories
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.16,0:07:15.03,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而这意味着来自某些目的地的飞行器将超越领土
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.03,0:07:18.21,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,at an altitude that might would be considered in orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.03,0:07:18.21,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在一个可能被认为是在轨道上的高度
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.68,0:07:21.15,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And this will probably lead to complaints from some
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.68,0:07:21.15,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而这可能会导致一些人的抱怨
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.45,0:07:24.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but there's basically very little that can be done to stop it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.45,0:07:24.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但基本上没有什么可以做的来阻止它
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.80,0:07:28.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,unless a country wants to actually go to war and deploy anti-satellite things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.80,0:07:28.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,除非一个国家想真正开战并部署反卫星的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.53,0:07:34.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Launching suborbital military rockets as well to fly over somebody else's territory
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.53,0:07:34.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,发射亚轨道军事火箭并飞越别人的领土
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:37.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,is also going to be a political minefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:37.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,也将是一个政治雷区
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.00,0:07:43.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Not just because it's like flying over other people's territory with military stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.00,0:07:43.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,不仅仅是因为它就像在别人的领土上飞过军事东西一样
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.53,0:07:47.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but hey how do that that's not a nuclear missile strike incoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.53,0:07:47.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但是 如何做到这一点 这不是一个核导弹袭击的到来
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.32,0:07:53.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The US actually has an ongoing project called Prompt Global Response(Strike)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.32,0:07:53.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,美国实际上有一个正在进行的项目 叫做全球快速反应（打击）
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.44,0:07:57.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,to deliver conventional weapons via something like an ICBM.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.44,0:07:57.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,以通过类似洲际弹道导弹的东西来运送常规武器
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.75,0:08:03.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And one of the major sticking points is the potential confusion and potential for retaliation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.75,0:08:03.69,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,其中一个主要的症结是潜在的混乱和报复的可能性
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.72,0:08:06.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,if another nation suspects that the launch is nuclear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.72,0:08:06.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,如果另一个国家怀疑发射的是核弹
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.35,0:08:12.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,When the global policy on averting nuclear conflict is mutually assured destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.35,0:08:12.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当避免核冲突的全球政策是相互确保摧毁时
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.77,0:08:18.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,there's not a huge room amount of room for nuance in responses to launches in other territories.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.77,0:08:18.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在对其他领土上的发射作出反应时 就没有很大的空间来进行微调
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.67,0:08:23.37,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So look I don't see this ever being deployed at least not in the near term.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.67,0:08:23.37,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 我认为这永远不会被部署 至少在短期内不会
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:27.99,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Technologically it's absolutely possible to build something that does this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:27.99,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,从技术上讲 制造这样的东西是绝对可能的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.16,0:08:30.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Starship isn't quite right for the task.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.16,0:08:30.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,星舰并不完全适合这项任务
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:35.01,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But if the DoD wanted I'm sure they could get something more in line with their needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:35.01,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但如果国防部想要 我相信他们可以得到更符合他们需求的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.34,0:08:37.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And there's a lot of defense contractors out there
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.34,0:08:37.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且有很多国防承包商在那里
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.56,0:08:40.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,that would be more than happy to take the money for such a project.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.56,0:08:40.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们会非常乐意接受这样一个项目的资金
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.86,0:08:45.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But I will say that I'd see suborbital transportation of military hardware
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.86,0:08:45.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但我想说的是 我认为军事硬件的亚轨道运输
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.70,0:08:50.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,as much more likely to happen than point-to-point civilian passenger transport
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.70,0:08:50.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,比点对点民用客运更有可能发生
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.24,0:08:53.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because you both actually have similar problems in terms of politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.24,0:08:53.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为你们在政治方面实际上都有类似的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.13,0:08:58.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But the military actually have the connections to help circumvent these problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.13,0:08:58.48,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但军方实际上有帮助规避这些问题的关系
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.01,0:09:01.23,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I'm Scott Manley. Fly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.01,0:09:01.23,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我是斯科特-曼利 飞行安全
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.70,0:09:20.41,1080P-sgbd-4s,,0,0,0,,[Music]
